This is a good movie. Will want to know what happens at the end. A certain female is very funny with her character. She played her part well. Glad to see John Amos still acting. Good Sunday evening movie  to watch after dinner.

I enjoyed this film. It's nice to see John Amos still making good films. The entire cast did a good job. Paula Jai Parker and Tamala Jones made the movie interesting. Each character is fully developed and they have their own problems. I liked how each person helped out their friends. This shows the importance of cultivating friendships in life. Your true friends can change your life for the better. Highly recommended for fans of comedies featuring an African American cast.
